publicDescription.summary: The Gates House is located in Bed-Stuy, a historic Brooklyn neighborhood that feels like home with its quaint streets and vibrant culture. This home offers spacious apartments with a serene outdoor area, spacious common areas and modern amenities — all tied together by our coliving community. As you enjoy all the Gates House has to offer, you’ll meet people from every corner of the world, building a community from the comfort of your home
publicDescription.space: The entire apartment (besides other bedrooms) is yours to call home! You'll have open access to the living room, kitchen and all other common areas.
publicDescription.interactionWithGuests: You'll always be able to reach our team if you have any questions! We also use Messenger within all of our houses, so you'll have a way to contact all of your housemates and our customer service team if needed
publicDescription.neighborhood: The Bedford House is in the charming and historic Bed-Stuy neighborhood, with the lively Herbert Von King park, trendy coffee shops like Brooklyn Blend and eclectic cuisine ranging from Caribbean to Japanese all within walking distance. If you feel like getting outside, you can take a stroll down Bed-Stuy's tree-lined streets and admire the brick and brownstone architecture the neighborhood is known for.
publicDescription.notes:
The well-being of our guests is our top priority, and we're committed to providing a safe environment for members at all Outpost houses as the novel coronavirus pandemic continues to evolve. We're following expert recommendations within our houses to ensure your safety, including by leaving rooms empty for at least 24 hours after a move-out, providing our staff with appropriate PPE and using high-strength Lysol/Clorox and bleach disinfectants (or alternatives) to clean after every guest departure. We'll continue to adapt our strategies moving forward to ensure the health and safety of all of our members.
Also:
1) we will request your phone and email address to add you to the remote lock system and to our maintenance portal
2) we will send you links to electronically sign our COVID form. The state government requires us to collect COVID related information for tracing purposes. 
3) upon arrival, we will request to check the photo ID's of each person that moves into the apartment to ensure safety of all members in the property. 
4) we may have security cameras in place - in common and public hallways, basements; in shared apartments, we may have cameras in living areas - in the kitchens and living rooms overlooking the kitchen and living room with 24/7 recording.

We care about the well-being and safety of all our tenants, and because of this, we request that everyone who lives at our spaces complete a Transunion background check. The background screening will not impact your credit score, and it’s free for you to complete. We will send you the link after you complete your reservation, along with a COVID waiver form, that is required by authorities for COVID tracing. For International guests we will request a copy of the valid USA visa.

Outpost Club does not accept bookings by one person for other people (third party bookings). If you would like to book an Outpost Club property, you must use your own Airbnb account to do so. During the move in, Outpost Club will require the person booking to present the same identification attached to the airbnb account. The only exception to this rule is for group bookings, though the person booking still must be part of the group moving in. If you are a parent who books for your children, but you will not stay in the property yourself, we will request you to pass a Transunion background check as well as sign guarantor agreement for your children.
publicDescription.houseRules:
1) Stay overnight is single only. No overnight guest stays. Price is per person. 
2) Wash dishes/kitchen appliances every time after food or drinks, clean the sink of the food remains every time after use. 
3) Separate the waste - there is a special container for Plastic, Glass, and Metal ONLY. 4) Turn off lights / TV in the main areas when not in use. 
5) Check and turn off the oven and gas when not in use.  
6) Fridge and Food shelves are divided between guests – please use your designated area, otherwise, if you leave the food outside your area – it can be removed during cleaning. 
7) Alcohol – being a health-oriented Club, we recommend minimizing alcohol consumption in Outpost Club. 
8) Don’t leave your staff in the common areas – it can be removed to the special Lost and Found boxes. 
9) Quiet hours – 10 pm – 8 am (no loud music, talks, TV… etc.) 
10)Smoking cigarettes, weed, and other substances are strictly prohibited anywhere in the Outpost Club.
11) Clean bathroom/toilet after each use and remove any dirt/hair etc.
12) Night check-in (after 9 pm) may be also organized for an extra fee of $30 USD. We can't guarantee check-in between 12:00 am and 9 am, however, if we are able to do it, there will be a $70 late check-in fee.

publicDescription.summary: This stylish place is close to must-see destinations. Cassa Studios and Residences powered by Outpost are just a short walk from Times Square in Manhattan, within easy reach of New York’s most popular attractions. Step outside and you’ll find yourself pulled instantly into the unique energy of the city, surrounded by all the shopping, dining, nightlife and entertainment you could hope for. It is also just minutes from the Javits Center
publicDescription.space: Bedrooms are available with full, queen and king-sized beds, depending on if you’re looking for a single, double or suite.
publicDescription.interactionWithGuests: You'll always be able to reach our team if you have any questions! We also use Messenger within all of our houses, so you'll have a way to contact all of your housemates and our customer service team if needed
publicDescription.neighborhood:
Walk out of the Cassa Studios and you’ll immediately feel the vibrancy and energy that draws tens of millions of people to New York City every year from all around the world. Our exhilarating city is home to more than 8 million people from all different cultures and backgrounds, who all make this vibrant metropolis a place like no other.

Whether you’re craving Italian or Uzbeki food, bubble tea or a classic New York slice, you can find it nearby. And if you’re looking to enjoy the great outdoors, you don’t have to go far! Central Park is just uptown, while Bryant Park, famous for its seasonal gardens and markets, is just three blocks away. You can even walk just 15 minutes through Hell’s Kitchen to the brand new Pier 76, overlooking the Hudson River.

Hell’s Kitchen is world-renowned for its vibrant LGBTQ+ scene, with plentiful bars and clubs that keep New York’s world-class nightlife scene right at your fingertips. The neighborhood is also home to a wide variety of locally owned small businesses, which remain relatively affordable compared to many parts of Manhattan.

If you’re in the mood for even more shopping, you can head to the famed district on the Upper East Side, or stay nearby and check out the shops at Hudson Yards, in the shadow of a mesmerizing 150-foot-tall honeycomb-like structure called the Vessel.

Whatever your mood, there will always be something for you in New York — we look forward to welcoming you!
publicDescription.transit:
The Cassa Studios are in a prime location to easily get around all of New York City, whether you’re staying in Manhattan or exploring the many exciting offerings of the outer boroughs. You can walk a few minutes to the Times Square/42nd Street subway station, which offers access to the most lines of any station in New York. From Times Square, you can catch the 1, 2, 3, 7, A, C, E, N, Q, R and W trains, as well as the shuttle train to Grand Central — meaning that for $2.75, you’re just steps away from getting anywhere in Manhattan, Brooklyn, Queens or the Bronx.

All-inclusive travel distance to popular destinations:
Empire State Building: 15 min. walking or via the N/Q/R
Central Park: 17 min. via the N/R
Lincoln Center: 15 min. via the 1
Met Museum: 30 min. via the 7 and 4/5/6
Washington Square Park: 16 min. via the A/C/E
Brooklyn Bridge: 25 min. via the A/C
publicDescription.notes:
-All guests of Cassa Studios and Residences must provide evidence of completion of the NYC Travelers Health Form prior to checking in. We'll send you an email with additional details.

-The rooftop is open seasonally. The gym is open 24/7. 

-Pets are not allowed in this building. We welcome service dogs, please contact us in advance if you have a service dog.

-The remaining balance of Taxes (NY Sales Tax: 8.875%, NYC City Tax: 5.875%, Occupancy Tax: $2.00) will be charged upon arrival.

-If you are staying for less than 25 days, you will need to pay the full amount of your stay, plus a $400 security deposit. If you are staying for more than 25 days, you will need to pay for the first 25 days, plus a $400 security deposit.

-Night check-in (after 9 p.m.) may also be organized for an extra fee of $30 USD. We can't guarantee check-in between 12 a.m. and 9 a.m.; however, if we are able to do it, there will be a $70 late check-in fee.

-Smoking, parties, and excessive noise are not allowed, including on balconies and in shared spaces. Smoking violations are subject to a $250 fine plus the cost to clean, deodorize, and repair damages.

-Guests are responsible for covering the cost to replace lost keys, key cards, fobs, or parking passes. Lost key replacement is $29, but might be waived the first time if requested during normal hours. However, if a resident is requesting key replacement outside of work hours it is subject to a mandatory $75 fee, paid upfront. 

-If you are staying for more than 25 days -  the background check will require your Social Security Number and a valid ID if you are American, or a passport and valid visa if you are international. Your information processed by TransUnion, one of the three large American credit bureaus, which is heavily regulated to protect your personal information. This information is required by us due to the number of scams we have been the victim of, and we have done our best to make the process as quick and easy as possible. You will be asked for this information after booking, and by making a reservation you are agreeing to complete a background check as part of the process.

-We try to make prices as low as possible, and therefore there is reduced services, like no standard reception, cleaning every ten days, no room service, no laundry service, limited number of towels etc. think of it this way, the more things you can you on your own, the less money you need to pay for it!

checkInInstructions.notes:
Welcome to Cassa Studios, powered by Outpost! We’re glad you’re joining our New York coliving community. We want to create spaces where people never feel alone — as we all are stronger together. We hope you enjoy your time with us! 

First, your new address! You will be living at 515 9th Ave, New York, NY 10018

Your house leaders' names are Isabela and Brenda, their phone numbers are +1 929-928-7165 and +1 347-879-1022. You can call, text, or contact them on WhatsApp. They are available 9am-9pm Monday-Friday. Outside of those hours you might be charged for additional/extended service, including keys. 

We communicate with each other via our house’s Messenger or WhatsApp group, which your House Leader will add you to upon your arrival. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!

Your Guest Portal is where you can pay your rent,  submit maintenance and cleaning requests RSVP for community events, and access important documents. Find it here. 

Your House Leader will meet you upon your arrival. Here’s what they can help you with: 
Info about community events 
Restocking supplies 
Questions about Cassa Studios

We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Guest Portal and your house’s Messenger group to keep up with what’s going on, or just ask your House Leader!
